## Global Rules

1. Do not use emojis in code, comments, commit messages, or responses.
2. Follow the hybrid SSR/SSG rendering strategy: `/post/[slug]` is prerendered (SSG); all other pages are SSR.
3. All GraphQL data fetching goes through `src/services/querys/` functions via the `src/services/wordpress.ts` client. Do not call `WPGRAPHQL_URL` directly from components or pages.
4. All SCSS imports must use the `@sass` alias: `@use "@sass/variables" as v;`. Never use relative paths.
5. WordPress Gutenberg content and title fields must be rendered with `set:html`, never with template interpolation `{}`.
6. New shared components go in `src/shared/components/` or `src/shared/ui/`. Page-specific components go in the page's local `_components/` directory.
7. Do not expose WordPress credentials, tokens, or the `WPGRAPHQL_URL` to client-side code. Use Astro SSR API routes as proxies.
8. Protected pages and API routes must validate the `accessToken` cookie via `isLoggedIn()` on every server render.
9. Run `pnpm build` or at minimum `astro check` before declaring any task complete.
10. After modifying database schemas, env vars, routing, or API definitions, update the corresponding documentation page in the Obsidian notes directory.

